Command registration

Command logic

movetoAngle function

{ “version”: “2025.0”, “command”: { “type”: “sequential”, “data”: { “commands”: [ { “type”: “path”, “data”: { “pathName”: “1M Forward” } }, { “type”: “named”, “data”: { “name”: null } } ] } }, “resetOdom”: true, “folder”: null, “choreoAuto”: false } There is a named command under null

posts.name: Krish
posts.cooked: How does one go about fixing this?

To fix the namecommand naming issue, go into pathplanner GUI and go into your autos that you want that command in, and add new Named Command under the same name as the command you want to run. Pathplanner should handle the rest

posts.name: Krish
posts.cooked: I figured out my problem Make sure your adding requirements to your commands if not it will default to your command I believe I didn’t notice this initially in teleop because I was doing .whileTrue on my triggers calling the command over and over again therefore not ending (might be wrong on that)  anyways make sure you add subsystem requirements to your code
